      "The hotel's unusual architectural pedigree, a Walter Gropius building, is less visible than it might be. Thierry Despont's 2011 interior is Art Deco-inflected and does not foreground the Bauhaus credentials of the shell. Most guests staying here do not register that they are staying inside a Gropius building. The exterior remains recognisably modernist but is not a dominant visual feature of Park Lane.",
