      "The fifteen guest rooms are distributed through the original inn building above and behind the restaurant. The design register is Lady Bamford's: pale neutrals, natural linens, organic cotton bedding, restrained ornamentation, plenty of space for a fifteen-room property. Bathrooms are generous relative to the inn's footprint. Some rooms have exposed timber beams from the original structure; all are quiet, as the building is set back from Kingham's village road.",
      "The village of Kingham itself is one of the Cotswolds' more interesting recent destinations, partly because the cluster of gastropubs here (The Wild Rabbit, the Kingham Plough, the Tollgate) has concentrated a specific kind of culinary tourism. Kingham station is a five-minute walk from the Wild Rabbit, with direct trains to London Paddington in 90 minutes, which makes the property one of the more accessible Cotswolds options from London.",
