    stayWardNote: "The Fife Arms operates rate parity across booking channels but is family-owned (Wirth) rather than group-operated, which typically means more room for negotiation than at a chain property. Private rates we have been quoted are typically 8 to 15 per cent below public rate on shoulder-season midweek dates, often with dinner inclusion, whisky tasting sessions, or a curator-led art tour included. The property is most negotiable in January to March and in shoulder autumn weeks; September is booked solid around the Braemar Gathering. Not guaranteed.",
