      "Cromlix sits in a small category of British hotels that are owned by non-hospitality owners who have made the hotel a serious personal project. Andy Murray, the tennis player born in Dunblane, three miles from the hotel, acquired the property in 2013 partly as a commercial investment and partly as a connection to the area that shaped him. Kim Murray has taken the creative lead on the hotel's direction, particularly through the 2023 redesign, and the hotel operates as an independent property rather than under any management group.",
