      "The Glasshouse restaurant, the hotel's dining room, serves modern Scottish cooking from chef Darin Campbell. The restaurant occupies a conservatory extension with views across the grounds and is one of the better hotel kitchens in central Scotland. The whisky bar, which adjoins the main drawing room, has a respectable Scotch selection.",
      "Cromlix's scale (15 rooms) and location (private grounds, no other structures visible, no village immediately adjacent) make it particularly well-suited to exclusive-use bookings. The property is regularly taken over for weddings, private events, and small corporate retreats; Murray's own wedding reception took place at the hotel in 2015. We handle exclusive-use briefs separately from standard room bookings.",
      "The property has no spa and no pool, though in-room treatments can be arranged. The gym is minimal. Cromlix is a country-house hotel in the traditional sense rather than a resort; guests who want spa and leisure infrastructure are better served at Gleneagles, 25 minutes' drive away.",
