      "The 1887 Restaurant, named for the year of the building's construction, operates at a level well above what its isolated location would suggest; the kitchen is run by Paul Green and has held AA rosettes consistently for over a decade. The cooking is Highland-produce-driven: venison, scallops, crab, grouse in season, foraged wild plants. The Whisky Bar holds a substantial collection of Highland malts with an emphasis on the distilleries of Wester Ross (GlenWyvis, Isle of Raasay, Ardnamurchan) which rarely appear in southern hotel collections.",
