      "The location places guests within easy reach of Helmsley (five miles), Rievaulx Abbey (eight miles), the Howardian Hills AONB, and the North York Moors National Park to the north. Castle Howard is 25 minutes' drive. York is 45 minutes. The Star at Harome is often used as a base for touring this north-east corner of Yorkshire rather than as a destination in itself, though the dinner-and-stay model means many guests never leave the village for the duration of their visit.",
