      "The house's literary association is with Lady Mary Wortley Montagu, the eighteenth-century writer and traveller (whose letters from Constantinople, written during her husband's ambassadorial posting, are among the most important eighteenth-century English-language travel writing). Montagu spent her childhood and early marriage at Middlethorpe between 1713 and 1715, before following her husband abroad. The hotel's literary connection is quieter and less marketed than the Balmoral's J.K. Rowling association but is authentic and well-documented.",
